## Tier-3 — competitive edge (true differentiation)

| Unit | Edge | Status |
|------|------|--------|
| T3-1 | **Benchora's `bencher`-format + sha256-baseline pipeline is genuinely rare in the Rust ecosystem** (most use only criterion's HTML output, lose history on `cargo clean`). SOTA 2026 = criterion 0.8 + custom storage; we exceed. | Documented |
| T3-2 | **portage is a fork of the actual Terminal-Bench `harbor` framework** — gives us the upstream eval SOTA (RL environments, agent harnesses) as a free base, plus our own request-id adoption (L7-001 propagation). | Documented |
| T3-3 | **pheno-harness 999-file Harbor fixture bundle** is a **non-trivial differentiation** — most teams use a handful of example tasks; 999 covers a wide surface for regression detection. | Documented |
| T3-4 | **Tracera polyglot (Rust+Python+Go+TS) on a single `Cargo.toml`/`pyproject.toml` workspace** with `tracera-core` as the canonical entity model = SOTA 2026 hexagonal pattern. | Documented |
| T3-5 | **phenodag's CGO-free `modernc.org/sqlite`** vs most Go DAG tools that link CGO SQLite — drops the CGO build dep, simplifies cross-compile, runs on any linux/amd64, linux/arm64, darwin, windows. | Documented |

## Tier-4 — deep SOTA opportunities (L4-tier, technical depth)

| Unit | SOTA gap | Why it matters | Status |
|------|----------|----------------|--------|
| L4-1 | **Benchora: criterion-html + JSON dual output** | criterion emits HTML by default; Benchora currently only emits JSON. SOTA 2026 (Divan 0.6, iai 0.6) supports both, and the HTML is the only thing most CI UIs (GitHub PR bot, Codecov) consume. | NEW |
| L4-2 | **Benchora: statistical-significance gate** (Welch's t-test on the bencher samples, not just delta%) | Delta% is a heuristic; a 3% regression in 1000 samples is noise, a 3% regression in 10 samples is real. SOTA 2026 = combined delta + p-value gate. | NEW |
| L4-3 | **Benchora: shared-baseline cross-crate mode** | Baselines today are per-crate (`./.benchora/<crate>.sqlite`). Real-world teams share one baseline across a workspace of 20+ crates. SOTA 2026 = `benchora baseline --workspace` + a content-addressed store keyed by (crate, profile, target-triple). | NEW |
| L4-4 | **portage: Harbor upstream-tracking bot** | Upstream Harbor is moving fast; today we manually check `git fetch upstream`. A nightly GitHub Action that diffs `origin/main` vs `upstream/main` and posts a PR description template would keep us 1 commit behind instead of 50. | NEW |
| L4-5 | **portage: evaluator-result schema-versioning** | Result JSONs today embed a `schema_version: 1`. As soon as we add a new field (e.g. `model_throughput_tokens_per_sec`), old eval results become silently incompatible. SOTA 2026 = explicit `SCHEMA.md` + migration tests in CI. | NEW |
| L4-6 | **pheno-harness: Harbor fixture-fidelity diff** | 999 files is great coverage but we don't track **which** upstream Harbor task each fixture is derived from. When Harbor changes a task's `instruction.md`, our fixtures drift silently. SOTA 2026 = a `harbor_upstream.json` manifest per fixture with the upstream SHA + a CI check. | NEW |
| L4-7 | **Tracera: semantic-scorer model hot-swap** | The `SemanticScorer` (DAG-T6) loads `BAAI/bge-small-en-v1.5` by default. Different teams need different embedding backbones (e.g. e5-large, mxbai). SOTA 2026 = `tracera score --model BAAI/bge-base-en-v1.5 --cache ./model_cache/` + lazy download + LRU. | NEW |
| L4-8 | **Tracera: trace-diff visualization** | Today the diff between two requirement-trace snapshots is a JSON patch. SOTA 2026 (Ibis 1.4, Deps 0.9) is an interactive HTML view with green/red highlighted requirements. | NEW |
| L4-9 | **phenodag: HTTP API + SQLite replication** | phenodag is a CLI tool with SQLite-as-source-of-truth. To coordinate with pheno-harness (eval pipeline) and Benchora (regression gates), it needs an HTTP API. SOTA 2026 = chi (Go) + sqlite-wal replication, single binary, OOB auth. | NEW |
| L4-10 | **phenodag: cross-project dependency edges** | Today phenodag is per-project (one SQLite per project). The L7-001 propagation spec implies cross-project edges (e.g. `Benchora` blocks `portage` which blocks `pheno-harness`). SOTA 2026 = a single root DB with `project_id` columns + foreign keys across project boundaries. | NEW |
| L4-11 | **heliosBench: GPU/ML-perf backend** | heliosBench today covers psutil/rich (CPU, mem, disk, net). SOTA 2026 local perf tools also cover GPU (nvidia-smi), ML (torch profiler integration), and storage IOPS (fio wrapper). | NEW |
| L4-12 | **AgilePlus: DAG-viz export** | AgilePlus stores the spec DAG in JSON. SOTA 2026 spec tools (e.g. OpenSpec, Speclane) export to Mermaid, Graphviz DOT, and D3-force HTML. Useful for review. | NEW (deferred — owned by AgilePlus lane) |
| L4-13 | **vibeproxy: OpenTelemetry export** | vibeproxy is a Prometheus-format metrics pipeline. SOTA 2026 is OTLP/HTTP (OpenTelemetry) so it can fan into Datadog, Honeycomb, Grafana Cloud, etc. The schema is similar (counters/histograms/labels) so the migration is mechanical. | NEW |
| L4-14 | **byteport: e2e-test scaffolding** | BytePort has a hybrid Tauri+Go+TS architecture but no e2e test harness. SOTA 2026 (Tauri 2.0 + WebDriverIO) gives us a single `tauri-driver` binary that drives the desktop app + Playwright for the SvelteKit UI. | NEW |
| L4-15 | **nanovms: post-quantum signature pass-through** | nanovms is the WASM/gVisor/Firecracker abstraction layer. As supply-chain attacks increase, SOTA 2026 demands sigstore/Rekor pass-through for image verification. nanovms is the natural place to bolt this on because it's the trust boundary. | NEW |
| L4-16 | **pheno-tracing: distributed-sampling-policy** | ADR-036 pheno-tracing is a port of OpenTelemetry sampling-policy. SOTA 2026 is consistent-probability sampling across spans (parent/child) — currently we sample independently per span, which biases the trace distribution. | NEW (deferred — owned by pheno-tracing lane) |

